"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the lmplot function from seaborn. The lmplot function is a figure-level function that creates a new figure for each facet, while the regplot function is an axes-level function that draws on an existing axes. If the intention is to create a single plot with multiple facets, lmplot is appropriate, but if the intention is to overlay multiple regression plots on the same axes, regplot should be used instead.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sns.lmplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', col='time', row='sex')\\n---\\n> sns.regplot(data=tips, x='total_bill', y='tip', ax=plt.gca())\"\n}"